import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';
---
<BlogPostLayout
  title="How to play as Yap Yap - Halo Wars 2"
  description="Master Yap Yap in Halo Wars 2 with this guide covering Grunt Goblins, Cannon Fodder swarms, Surprise Party mines, and the powerful 'death by a thousand cuts' playstyle."
  category="Guides"
  publishedDate="Published on January 31, 2026"
  dateIso="2026-01-31"
  ogImage="/img/HW-Guides/Yap Yap-2.jpg"
  youtubeId="OZEoTTjItz4"
  tags={['Halo Wars 2']}
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Yap Yap is one of the last leaders added into Halo Wars 2. His strength is "death by a thousand cuts" - he has many annoying powers, unit buffs, and units that work really well together.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">Key Strengths</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Grunt Goblins (Hero Units)</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Among the best hero units in the game</li>
    <li>Not for their attack, but for their Y ability</li>
    <li>Healing is incredibly fast</li>
    <li>You get THREE Grunt Goblins</li>
    <li>Can heal bases, Scarabs, units - anything that needs healing</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Cannon Fodder</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Yap Yap starts with 5 Cannon Fodder instead of the normal 3 Grunts</li>
    <li>They're FREE units</li>
    <li>Weak, but that's the point - they're cannon fodder</li>
    <li>Use them for annoyances, scouting, grabbing power crates, and swarming</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Build Order</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Early Game</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Build two Harvesters, then one Power Extractor</li>
    <li>Send Cannon Fodder everywhere: supplies, power, expos, scouting</li>
    <li>Queue up 6-8 Cannon Fodder while getting economy going</li>
    <li>Upgrade your Harvester</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Infantry Rush Build</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Build two Raid Camps</li>
    <li>Pump out Cannon Fodder and mix in Choppers</li>
    <li>Alternate between Heavy Grunts and Grunt Riders</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Key Units</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Heavy Grunts:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Consume NO power</li>
    <li>Tougher, flexible ground troops</li>
    <li>Quick capture units</li>
    <li>With Party's Over upgrade, get EMP Y ability that stuns vehicles and aircraft</li>
    <li>Great against Vulture spam</li>
    <li>With EMP upgrade, become GREEN (effective) against air</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Grunt Riders:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Cost 75 pop</li>
    <li>Good early aggression unit</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Leader Powers</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">First Point: Surprise Party</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Drops a single mine</li>
    <li>When triggered, spawns veteran Cannon Fodder squads</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Critical:</strong> Get Surprise Party 2 with your second point
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2">
        <li>Adds a second mine</li>
        <li>Spawns Vet 3 Cannon Fodder</li>
        <li>Mines are very powerful (can make ODST squads vanish)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Vet 3 Cannon Fodder Tips</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>They're temporary (on a timer)</li>
    <li>Don't underestimate them</li>
    <li>Send them to attack opponent's base - worst case you scout, best case you get some kills</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Third Point: Shade Drop</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Drops four turrets</li>
    <li>Gives four more targets for your opponent to shoot</li>
    <li>Turrets distract from your squads</li>
    <li>Can be used defensively when retreating</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Fourth Point: Grunts from Above</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Deploys Heavy Grunts, Grunt Riders, and Methane Wagon</li>
    <li>Great way to get Methane Wagons without the separate power</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Fifth Point: Methane Party</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Similar animation to Forge's Scatter Bomb</li>
    <li>Drops methane that debuffs enemies</li>
    <li>Increases Grunt combat effectiveness</li>
    <li>Synergizes with Yap Yap's ground infantry strength</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Other Notable Powers</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Grunt Dome</strong>: Shield from damage, great for your army or allies</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Glassing Beam</strong>: Get to Level 3</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Please Don't Shoot Me</strong>: Good if losing and need extra time (get later)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Cannon Fodder Upgrades</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Worth Investing In</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>First upgrade: 400 power</li>
    <li>Second upgrade (Refer a Friend): 600 power - grants passive self-healing</li>
    <li>When fully upgraded, surprisingly effective</li>
    <li>Can do significant damage even against a Condor</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Tech 2 and Beyond</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Transition</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Get Shield Generator</li>
    <li>Build War Council and Foundry</li>
    <li>Sacrifice one Raid Camp for a Harvester (early rush only works once)</li>
    <li>Get your three Grunt Goblins immediately</li>
    <li>Get the Grunt Hustle ability</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Engineers</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Don't forget to build Engineers</li>
    <li>Engineer shield + Methane Wagons + Grunt Goblin Y ability = Dangerous combination</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Infantry Focus</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Keep a Raid Camp on hand</li>
    <li>Get infantry upgrades (works for Cannon Fodder too)</li>
    <li>Heavy Grunts and Hunters are key</li>
    <li>Elite Rangers don't have upgrades for any Banished leader</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Tech 3</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Wraiths</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Still really good</li>
    <li>Mix Wraiths with your infantry</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Countering Threats</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>If opponent goes vehicles: Use Hunters or a few Banshees</li>
    <li>If opponent goes air: Heavy Grunts with Party's Over are excellent</li>
    <li>Reavers are your best bet for dedicated anti-air</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Army Composition Tips</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">DO:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Focus on Grunt Goblins</li>
    <li>Invest in infantry</li>
    <li>Make sure you can counter vehicles</li>
    <li>Use Methane Wagons as support</li>
    <li>Combine healing abilities (Engineer shield + Methane Wagon + Grunt Goblin Y)</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">DON'T:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Go mass air - that's not Yap Yap's strength</li>
    <li>Neglect counters for enemy vehicles</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Summary</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Yap Yap's individual abilities may not seem broken (except the Grunt Goblins' healing), but combining everything makes him a really strong leader. His annoyances stack up through free units, powerful mines, infantry buffs, and incredible healing capability. Focus on ground game, use your free Cannon Fodder wisely, and don't underestimate the power of stacking his various abilities together.
  </p>
</BlogPostLayout>
